laboratory_examinations.findings: Endometrial line of the uterine cavity poorly displayed; liquid dark area in the uterine cavity measuring about 88 mm × 63 mm × 86 mm, with fair translucency and a few punctate echoes visible.
Revealed cervical cancer invading the upper third of the vagina.

Minimal deviation adenocarcinoma of the cervix measuring 4.5 cm × 4 cm × 2 cm, invading the lower uterine body, with intravascular embolism. Cancer metastases detected in 2/11 left pelvic lymph nodes, 2/9 right pelvic lymph nodes, and 2/2 common iliac lymph nodes. Cancerous tissue was <1 mm from the circumferential incision margin.

CEA (+), P16 (−), Ki67-MIB1 (hot zone 30%), ER (−), P53 (−), PR (−), Vimentin (−), Bcl-2 (−), CK7 (+), Muc-6 (partial +), CK20 (−), CDX2 (−), Villin (−), Napsin-A (−), Muc-1 (+), Muc-2 (−), Muc-5AC (+).
